,"text":". (Nh, L.) It is applied in this sense to night (Nh, L) [and also to day: to each in the Kur xxviii. 71 and 72]: and to night as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Long."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) ―         -b3-  Accord. to El-Fakhr Er-Rázee, it is derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~arodu","text_ar":"السَّرْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which denotes consecutiveness and uninterruptedness, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"is added to give intensiveness to the signification: if so, its proper place is in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srd","text_ar":"سرد"},{"kind":"text","text":"; its measure being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEomalN","text_ar":"فَعْمَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (MF:) [thus] its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"is augmentative like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dulaAmiSN","text_ar":"دُلَامِصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Bd in xxviii. 71.) ―         -b4-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa laka saromadFA","text_ar":"هُوَ لَكَ سَرْمَدًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, is thine ever,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for ever."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smd","text_ar":"سمد"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["Kh","M","L","Nh","MF"]}]}}